"Join us June 29 at 3pm CEST/ 9am EDT for a guided introduction to using the Open Science Indicators dashboard prototype, and to hear from a library leader on how institutions are already using open science monitoring to inform reporting, planning, and open science strategy.

In this one-hour session hosted by PLOS Sr. Open Research Manager Lauren Cadwallader and Regional Sales Director Marco Castellan along with guest speaker Laetitia Bracco, Deputy Head of the Library Research Support Services at the University of Lorraine, you’ll learn how to: 1. Identify open science trends across your institution 2. Explore researcher engagement with open science practices 3. Benchmark activity against similar organizations&nbsp;

4. Understand how open science practices are evolving across research communities"
